  <comment type="function">
    <text evidence="2 4 5">Peptide antibiotic that functions through inhibition of the bacterial DNA-dependent RNA polymerase (RNAP) (PubMed:21396375, PubMed:30626643). Inhibits transcription by binding in RNAP secondary channel, where it sterically blocks the folding of the trigger loop, which is essential for efficient catalysis (PubMed:21396375, PubMed:30626643). In contrast to MccJ25, does not restrict access of nucleotide substrates to the catalytic center and shows a non-competitive mode of inhibition (PubMed:30626643). Shows activity against closely related Gram-negative Burkholderia and Pseudomonas strains (PubMed:18671394). Is not active against Gram-positive bacteria (PubMed:18671394).</text>
  </comment>
